---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Prompt from '../components/Prompt.astro';
---
<Base title="About — John Soh" description="John Soh is a senior DevRel and AI engineer at Virtuals Protocol, working on the Agent Commerce Protocol.">
  <Prompt text="cat about.md" />
  <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:16px; margin:8px 0 20px;">
    <div style="width:52px; height:52px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--raise); border:1px solid var(--accent); display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;" class="mono" aria-hidden="true">
      <span style="color:var(--accent); font-size:15px;">JS</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h1 style="font-size:20px;">John Soh</h1>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:12px; color:var(--dim);">sr devrel + ai engineer @ virtuals</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="prose" style="color:var(--dim); max-width:60ch;">
    <p>
      I'm a Senior DevRel Engineer at Virtuals Protocol, where I build the
      developer community around AI agents and the Agent Commerce Protocol (ACP)
      — the infrastructure that lets agents transact with each other
      autonomously. I wear two hats: I run the hackathons, talks, and docs that
      get developers building, and I engineer the AI systems underneath — RAG
      pipelines, autonomous evaluator agents, and multi-agent workflows running
      in production.
    </p>
    <p>
      Before Virtuals I was a software engineer at Veritas Technologies,
      shipping full-stack features and REST APIs for enterprise software. That
      mix — production engineering plus developer advocacy — is the whole point
      for me: I care most about the moment a developer goes from reading about a
      protocol to having it work on their machine, and most of what I build and
      write is about shrinking that gap.
    </p>
  </div>
  <p style="margin:24px 0 14px;">
    <a class="btn" href="/resume.pdf" download>↓ download resume</a>
  </p>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:12px; color:var(--dim);">
    <a href="https://github.com/johnsoh">github ↗</a> ·
    <a href="https://twitter.com/johnsoh">twitter ↗</a> ·
    <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/johnsoh">linkedin ↗</a> ·
    <a href="/rss.xml">rss</a>
  </p>
</Base>
